  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ocean Plastic Turned into an Opportunity in Circular Economy (OPTOCE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project &quot;Ocean Plastic Turned into an Opportunity in Circular Economy (OPTOCE) is part of the Norwegian development assistance program against marine litter and microplastics. It aims to increase the capturing rate and treatment capacity for plastic waste and to use public private partnerships to collect waste from polluted hot-spots, major rivers basins and beach front areas. Pilot demonstrations will be established for treatment of plastic waste in local industries.</narrative>
  </description>
